        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Defense vs welfare</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/troop-increase-domestic-international-military-deployment.png" alt="The number of troops will be increased both inside and outside the country" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>The number of troops will be increased both inside and outside the country. Credits: Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Belgium’s Budget Minister, Vincent Van Peteghem, warned that a sharp rise in defense spending <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-17-04-2025-h2-4-could-harm" target="_blank">could harm</a> the country’s welfare state. His comments come after the government decided to meet NATO’s 2% of GDP defense spending target. “Every euro we spend will add to our debt. This debt will lead to higher taxes or cuts in social welfare,” he stated.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">He acknowledged the need for defense spending but emphasized the importance of social protections. This decision follows pressure from the US and other NATO allies to increase military expenditure, mainly due to Russia’s ongoing war in Ukraine.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">While Spain and Italy plan to expand the scope of their spending by including cybersecurity and border patrol, countries bordering Russia, like Estonia, want to focus on military spending. Moreover, other European nations want to reduce their military dependency on the US.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
